    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - BODY FEATURES - CLUTCH SWITCH -
        CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08258a8" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
        <figure id="f08290940" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/g08290940.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Clutch Switch Function Diagram</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CLUTCH SWITCH MODULE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ENGINE CONTROL MODULE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290073.xml" xrefid="f08290940">Clutch Switch Function Diagram</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>The clutch switch module contains two clutch switches. One switch is an input to the ESC and senses clutch
            pedal position to disengage the cruise control. The other clutch switch is an input to the engine controller
            and senses clutch pedal position to enable engine cranking.
        </para>
        <para>Both switches are magnetic and require no adjustment.</para>
